The paper deals with hypergraphs and coloring, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The concept of nearly-intersecting hypergraphs is related to intersection graphs, which are often studied in computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also uses techniques from graph theory and combinatorics, which are common in the subfield of theoretical computer science known as graph theory (cs.GT). The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests that it could also be classified under data structures (cs.DS) or machine learning (cs.LG), as these subfields often deal with efficient algorithms.
